      },
      "correct": "B",
      "explanation": "By definition, partial sum adds first n terms.",
      "notesSection": "10.1 - Sequences and Series",
      "notesSnippet": "Partial sums determine convergence behavior.",
      "timeTip": "Write first few terms to avoid confusion."
    },
    {
      "section": "10.2",
      "topic": "Geometric Series",
      "calcType": "No Calculator",
      "question": "sum_{n=0}^infinity (1/3)^n converges to:",
      "choices": {
        "A": "1/2",
        "B": "3/2",
        "C": "1",
        "D": "Diverges"
      },
      "correct": "B",
      "explanation": "Infinite geometric sum is 1/(1-r)=1/(1-1/3)=3/2.",
      "notesSection": "10.2 - Geometric Series",
      "notesSnippet": "Use |r|<1 and a/(1-r).",
      "timeTip": "Identify a and r carefully."
    },
